name: architecture#2
description:
Iranian architecture is one of the oldest arts and we are witnessing it with the prosperity of traditional architecture from ancient times.
Throughout its history, Iranian architecture has always been associated with the originality of design and simplicity along with the implementation of the principles of Iranian architecture and has gone through many ups and downs, but has always acted and reacted peacefully with nature and in accordance with the needs of each period. In connection with nature; Traditional Iranian architecture in all areas and cities, especially villages and old and ancient monuments such as living books, but worn by the history of Iranian architecture.
Traditional Iranian architecture dates back to around the seventh millennium BC and has undergone many changes over the years until it has grown to its current form.
